        "**Exchange Rate vs. Inflation Rate (India):**\n",
        "\n",
        "The correlation is about -0.34, which means there is a weak negative relationship. This suggests that when inflation in India goes up, the value of the Indian Rupee (INR) tends to go down against the US Dollar (USD). However, this relationship is not very strong, meaning other factors also play a significant role in determining the exchange rate.\n",
